Fifty governorship candidates from various political parties on Wednesday signed a peace accord in Sokoto state. They include candidates for the two major political parties in the state, Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and his former deputy, Ahmed Aliyu, who is contesting under the banner of All Progressives Congress (APC) as well as four female candidates.  Details later… Sokoto governorship candidates to sign peace accord Kogi governorship: Candidates sign peace accord PHOTOS: Scenes from Peace Accord Meeting